1)  Find a parking spot and pull over the car in a safe place.
2)  Once the car is stopped, open the door and walk back in front of the trunk.
3)  While the trunk is lock or it is closed:
    •	Use the key or press the bottom to unlock and open it
	
4)  Take out the wrench, jack and spare tire.
5)  Place the Jack under your car.
6)  Lock the lever of the jack in the hole of the jack.
7)  Keep the lever with you left hand and rotate the lever with your right hand.
8)  Until the car is moved up enough so the flat tire is loose:
    •	Jack-up the car 

9)  Pick the wrench and use it to unscrew all the lug nuts.
10) If the lug nuts are loose and out:
    •	Pull the flat tire so you can to take it off.
    Else
    •	Unscrew the remaining lug nuts

11) Put on the spare tire.
12) Pick the wrench and screw the lug nuts, if all the lug nuts are screw tight:
    •	Go to the next step.
    Else
    •	Screw the remaining lug nuts tight

13) Use the jack and lever and rotate to the exact opposite direction and until the car is move down on the ground:
    •	Use jack to lower the car.

14) Put the jack and wrench right at their same place and replace the flat tire in the trunk.
15) Close the truck of your car, voila, you're good to go!
